Locations.Subject: ELA
Locations.UnitDescription: In this unit we will learn how the same story is often told across cultures and from different points of view.  For example, how would the wolf tell the story of The Three Little Pigs?

Locations.Subject: ELA
Locations.UnitDescription: There are signs and symbols all around usfrom television ads to traffic signals to computer icons. In this unit, we will explore the ways in which symbols express who we are, what we like, what we believe, and what we do.

Locations.Subject: ELA
Locations.UnitDescription: Smart, smarter, smartest. Thats our goal for this unit: to improve our ability to think and to learn. We will be studying the different ways people learn, what makes them learn better, why some people have an easier time learning things, why some people are better at math but not so great at poetry, and vice versa. How will you get better at something this month?
